   442→## [8.6.0](https://github.com/motdotla/dotenv/compare/v8.5.1...v8.6.0) (2021-05-05)
   443→
   444→### Added
   445→
   446→- define package.json in exports
   447→
   448→## [8.5.1](https://github.com/motdotla/dotenv/compare/v8.5.0...v8.5.1) (2021-05-05)
   449→
   450→### Changed
   451→
   452→- updated dev dependencies via npm audit
   453→
   454→## [8.5.0](https://github.com/motdotla/dotenv/compare/v8.4.0...v8.5.0) (2021-05-05)
   455→
   456→### Added
   457→
   458→- allow for `import "dotenv/config"`
   459→
   460→## [8.4.0](https://github.com/motdotla/dotenv/compare/v8.3.0...v8.4.0) (2021-05-05)
   461→
   462→### Changed
   463→
   464→- point to exact types file to work with VS Code
   465→
   466→## [8.3.0](https://github.com/motdotla/dotenv/compare/v8.2.0...v8.3.0) (2021-05-05)
   467→
   468→### Changed
   469→
   470→- _Breaking:_ drop support for Node v8 (mistake to be released as minor bump. later bumped to 9.0.0. see above.)
   471→
   472→## [8.2.0](https://github.com/motdotla/dotenv/compare/v8.1.0...v8.2.0) (2019-10-16)
   473→
   474→### Added
   475→
   476→- TypeScript types
   477→
   478→## [8.1.0](https://github.com/motdotla/dotenv/compare/v8.0.0...v8.1.0) (2019-08-18)
   479→
   480→### Changed
   481→
   482→- _Breaking:_ drop support for Node v6 ([#392](https://github.com/motdotla/dotenv/issues/392))
   483→
   484→# [8.0.0](https://github.com/motdotla/dotenv/compare/v7.0.0...v8.0.0) (2019-05-02)
   485→
   486→### Changed
   487→
   488→- _Breaking:_ drop support for Node v6 ([#302](https://github.com/motdotla/dotenv/issues/392))
   489→
   490→## [7.0.0] - 2019-03-12
   491→
   492→### Fixed
   493→
   494→- Fix removing unbalanced quotes ([#376](https://github.com/motdotla/dotenv/pull/376))
   495→
   496→### Removed
   497→
   498→- Removed `load` alias for `config` for consistency throughout code and documentation.
   499→
   500→## [6.2.0] - 2018-12-03
   501→
   502→### Added
   503→
   504→- Support preload configuration via environment variables ([#351](https://github.com/motdotla/dotenv/issues/351))
   505→
   506→## [6.1.0] - 2018-10-08
   507→
   508→### Added
   509→
   510→- `debug` option for `config` and `parse` methods will turn on logging
   511→
   512→## [6.0.0] - 2018-06-02
   513→
   514→### Changed
   515→
   516→- _Breaking:_ drop support for Node v4 ([#304](https://github.com/motdotla/dotenv/pull/304))
   517→
   518→## [5.0.0] - 2018-01-29
   519→
   520→### Added
   521→
   522→- Testing against Node v8 and v9
   523→- Documentation on trim behavior of values
   524→- Documentation on how to use with `import`
   525→
   526→### Changed
   527→
   528→- _Breaking_: default `path` is now `path.resolve(process.cwd(), '.env')`
   529→- _Breaking_: does not write over keys already in `process.env` if the key has a falsy value
   532→### Removed
   533→
   534→- Testing against Node v7
   535→
   536→## [4.0.0] - 2016-12-23
   537→
   538→### Changed
   539→
   540→- Return Object with parsed content or error instead of false ([#165](https://github.com/motdotla/dotenv/pull/165)).
   541→
   542→### Removed
   543→
   544→- `verbose` option removed in favor of returning result.
   545→
   546→## [3.0.0] - 2016-12-20
   547→
   548→### Added
   549→
   550→- `verbose` option will log any error messages. Off by default.
   551→- parses email addresses correctly
   552→- allow importing config method directly in ES6
   553→
   554→### Changed
   555→
   556→- Suppress error messages by default ([#154](https://github.com/motdotla/dotenv/pull/154))
   557→- Ignoring more files for NPM to make package download smaller
   559→### Fixed
   560→
   561→- False positive test due to case-sensitive variable ([#124](https://github.com/motdotla/dotenv/pull/124))
   562→
   563→### Removed
   564→
   565→- `silent` option removed in favor of `verbose`
   566→
   567→## [2.0.0] - 2016-01-20
   568→
   569→### Added
   570→
   571→- CHANGELOG to ["make it easier for users and contributors to see precisely what notable changes have been made between each release"](http://keepachangelog.com/). Linked to from README
   572→- LICENSE to be more explicit about what was defined in `package.json`. Linked to from README
   573→- Testing nodejs v4 on travis-ci
   574→- added examples of how to use dotenv in different ways
   575→- return parsed object on success rather than boolean true
   576→
   577→### Changed
   578→
   579→- README has shorter description not referencing ruby gem since we don't have or want feature parity
   580→
   581→### Removed
   582→
   583→- Variable expansion and escaping so environment variables are encouraged to be fully orthogonal
   584→
   585→## [1.2.0] - 2015-06-20
   586→
   587→### Added
   588→
   589→- Preload hook to require dotenv without including it in your code
   590→
   591→### Changed
   592→
   593→- clarified license to be "BSD-2-Clause" in `package.json`
   594→
   595→### Fixed
   596→
   597→- retain spaces in string vars
   598→
   599→## [1.1.0] - 2015-03-31
   600→
   601→### Added
   602→
   603→- Silent option to silence `console.log` when `.env` missing
   604→
   605→## [1.0.0] - 2015-03-13
   606→
   607→### Removed
   608→
   609→- support for multiple `.env` files. should always use one `.env` file for the current environment
